4 SYNOPSIS:
5 Under Article V of the United States
6 Constitution, if two-thirds of the states apply,
7 Congress must call a convention of the states to
8 propose amendments to the Constitution.
9 This bill would establish a process for the
10 appointment of commissioners and alternate
11 commissioners to serve as Alabama's delegation to an
12 Article V Convention.
13 This bill would establish qualifications for
14 commissioners, provide for duties of commissioners, and
15 provide for the recall and removal of commissioners.
16 This bill would require the Legislature, by
17 joint resolution, to appoint commissioners and
18 alternate commissioners and require the Legislature to
19 include certain information instructing commissioners
20 on their duties and scope of authority.
21 This bill would require commissioners and
22 alternate commissioners to execute an oath.
23 This bill would provide that commissioners and
24 alternate commissioners shall be compensated at the
25 same rate as members of the House of Representatives,
26 prorated by the length of time served, and this bill
27 would prohibit commissioners and alternate
28 commissioners from receiving certain gifts.
Page 1

commissioners from receiving certain gifts.
HB443 INTRODUCED
29 This bill would provide that the delegation may
30 select individuals to serve in leadership roles and
31 establish a quorum for decision-making.
32 This bill would create an advisory committee to
33 monitor an Article V Convention and the commissioners.
34 This bill would establish a procedure for
35 recalling and removing commissioners who exceed the
36 scope of their authority.
37 This bill would also establish criminal
38 penalties for commissioners who exceed the scope of
39 their authority and for individuals who interfere in
40 the performance of a commissioner's duty.
